00:36:59,467 --> 00:37:02,428
Do you mean the daughter
you abandoned when you were alive?

555
00:37:08,267 --> 00:37:09,977
I'd rather go back to Hell!

556
00:37:10,937 --> 00:37:12,146
I can't…

557
00:37:12,230 --> 00:37:14,732
I can't bear it anymore!

558
00:37:16,442 --> 00:37:17,860
Your life on Earth

559
00:37:18,736 --> 00:37:20,488
may have been your choice.

560
00:37:20,571 --> 00:37:22,573
But your life here

561
00:37:22,657 --> 00:37:23,908
is your responsibility.

562
00:37:24,909 --> 00:37:27,245
No matter how hard it gets,
you must endure it.

563
00:37:29,538 --> 00:37:31,457
Your true suffering

564
00:37:32,500 --> 00:37:34,460
begins now.

565
00:37:45,388 --> 00:37:46,305
Come on!

566
00:37:48,015 --> 00:37:50,935
The president
is really not here right now.

567
00:37:51,018 --> 00:37:53,729
After I talk to him today,

568
00:37:53,813 --> 00:37:55,731
I won't ever be coming back here.

569
00:37:55,815 --> 00:37:57,858
-So please let me enter.
-No!

570
00:37:58,401 --> 00:37:59,235
Please!

571
00:37:59,318 --> 00:38:02,822
-I mean it. He's really not here! Please!
-Geez.

572
00:38:04,490 --> 00:38:07,159
-What's wrong?
-Judging by how my heart is pounding,

573
00:38:07,243 --> 00:38:09,161
he must be nearby.

574
00:38:09,245 --> 00:38:10,329
What?

575
00:38:10,913 --> 00:38:11,789
What?

576
00:38:11,872 --> 00:38:12,999
What's wrong?

577
00:38:14,250 --> 00:38:15,793
Looks like he's over there.

578
00:38:17,545 --> 00:38:18,379
He's coming.

579
00:38:18,462 --> 00:38:20,089
What? He's coming.

580
00:38:20,172 --> 00:38:21,799
He's getting closer.

581
00:38:27,513 --> 00:38:29,098
See? Sweetie!

582
00:38:48,242 --> 00:38:49,201
Young-ae?

583
00:38:49,869 --> 00:38:51,746
Young-ae, is it really you?

584
00:39:12,725 --> 00:39:13,768
Hey, Young-ae.

585
00:39:15,102 --> 00:39:15,936
Young-ae.

586
00:39:17,063 --> 00:39:18,689
What's wrong? Got a stomachache?

587
00:39:21,942 --> 00:39:23,069
What's wrong with her?

588
00:39:26,739 --> 00:39:28,032
What's wrong?

589
00:39:33,079 --> 00:39:34,872
Young-ae, what's wrong?

590
00:39:34,955 --> 00:39:36,874
What's wrong?

591
00:39:36,957 --> 00:39:38,459
Tell me. Young-ae.

592
00:39:39,543 --> 00:39:40,628
What's going on?

593
00:39:40,711 --> 00:39:42,254
Goodness, what's wrong?

594
00:39:42,338 --> 00:39:45,174
Goodness, what's wrong? Stop it.

595
00:39:45,257 --> 00:39:48,302
What startled you so much? Tell us--

596
00:39:48,386 --> 00:39:50,763
-What's wrong?
-Why is she acting like this?

597
00:39:52,681 --> 00:39:54,308
Yes? Coming. I'll go.

598
00:39:54,392 --> 00:39:55,768
It's okay.

599
00:40:00,439 --> 00:40:01,273
Who are you?

600
00:40:01,857 --> 00:40:02,858
Is Young-ae here?

601
00:40:02,942 --> 00:40:04,568
-What? Hold on.
-Young-ae!

602
00:40:04,652 --> 00:40:07,154
What about Young-ae?
Who are you and what do you want with her?

603
00:40:07,238 --> 00:40:08,948
Please let me meet her.

604
00:40:09,031 --> 00:40:10,324
Hold on. Please wait here.

605
00:40:10,408 --> 00:40:11,242
Young-ae!

606
00:40:11,325 --> 00:40:13,160
-Stop!
-It's Dad! Can you hear me?!

607
00:40:13,244 --> 00:40:14,912
Young-ae!

608
00:40:14,995 --> 00:40:16,247
"Dad"?

609
00:40:16,330 --> 00:40:17,832
How are you here?

610
00:40:19,333 --> 00:40:20,751
How dare you call yourself her dad?

611
00:40:20,835 --> 00:40:22,044
Leave this instant!

612
00:40:22,128 --> 00:40:23,629
Ma'am, you know me.

613
00:40:23,712 --> 00:40:25,923
I know you, all right!

614
00:40:26,590 --> 00:40:28,884
Don't hurt Young-ae anymore and just go.

615
00:40:30,094 --> 00:40:32,430
I really need to talk to her.

616
00:40:32,513 --> 00:40:33,681
Leave!

617
00:40:34,557 --> 00:40:36,434
Young-ae!

618
00:40:38,686 --> 00:40:40,271
Are you okay?

619
00:40:41,188 --> 00:40:44,525
Young-ae! Your father is here!

620
00:40:47,194 --> 00:40:49,572
Where the hell are you?!

621
00:41:08,299 --> 00:41:09,133
He's gone.

622
00:41:09,216 --> 00:41:10,968
He's gone. Mr. Ko sent him away.

623
00:41:11,051 --> 00:41:12,011
Don't worry.

624
00:41:12,094 --> 00:41:13,554
It's okay. He's gone.

625
00:41:13,637 --> 00:41:15,264
You poor thing.

626
00:41:16,599 --> 00:41:17,558
He's gone. You're okay.

627
00:41:17,641 --> 00:41:19,059
You're all right.

628
00:41:28,027 --> 00:41:29,695
I screamed so much

629
00:41:30,362 --> 00:41:31,780
that I'm completely drained.

630
00:41:32,740 --> 00:41:33,741
I hate it.

631
00:41:34,617 --> 00:41:35,701
So much.

632
00:41:35,784 --> 00:41:37,328
I know how you feel.

633
00:41:37,411 --> 00:41:39,622
Hate your father all you want.

634
00:41:39,705 --> 00:41:41,832
No one will blame you.

635
00:41:41,916 --> 00:41:43,083
It's okay.

636
00:41:43,167 --> 00:41:44,919
-It's okay.
-Not him.

637
00:41:47,588 --> 00:41:48,589
I hate myself

638
00:41:50,257 --> 00:41:51,967
for just taking the beating

639
00:41:53,302 --> 00:41:54,470
without saying anything

640
00:41:55,513 --> 00:41:56,347
back then.

641
00:41:58,390 --> 00:41:59,391
I hate myself.

642
00:42:38,556 --> 00:42:41,559
Don't you know
doing this hurts her even more?

643
00:42:43,435 --> 00:42:45,896
I don't care what punishment I receive.

644
00:42:47,189 --> 00:42:50,526
But I can't let Young-ae get hurt
because of me, even after death.

645
00:42:50,609 --> 00:42:53,070
She says she can't forgive you.

646
00:42:53,153 --> 00:42:55,447
You're selfish to the very end.

647
00:42:57,074 --> 00:42:59,118
What? Did you
turn over a new leaf after dying?

648
00:42:59,201 --> 00:43:00,911
Why apologize now?

649
00:43:03,998 --> 00:43:04,832
Yes.

650
00:43:05,833 --> 00:43:08,460
I should take this up with the person
who sent you here.

651
00:43:08,544 --> 00:43:09,712
That's the right thing to do.

652
00:43:10,296 --> 00:43:11,505
-Young-ae--
-Get up.

653
00:43:12,131 --> 00:43:13,549
-Follow me.
-Hey.

654
00:43:14,675 --> 00:43:15,759
Young-ae.

655
00:43:23,517 --> 00:43:26,478
I guess I have to cause
this much of a scene to see you,

656
00:43:26,562 --> 00:43:28,606
Mr. Great President.

657
00:43:29,440 --> 00:43:31,775
I have a lot on my plate.

658
00:43:33,652 --> 00:43:35,112
Well, you're gonna get busier now.

659
00:43:37,323 --> 00:43:39,366
How could such a sinful man like him

660
00:43:39,450 --> 00:43:42,036
brazenly be
walking around Heaven like this?

661
00:43:42,745 --> 00:43:45,414
He should still be burning
in the flames of Hell.

662
00:43:46,081 --> 00:43:47,625
He was already burned.

663
00:43:48,208 --> 00:43:49,251
Roasted, even.

664
00:43:50,753 --> 00:43:55,507
Does he look happy to you right now?

665
00:43:55,591 --> 00:43:57,217
He shouldn't be happy!

666
00:43:58,594 --> 00:43:59,428
You're right.

667
00:44:00,054 --> 00:44:01,305
If he's still unhappy,

668
00:44:02,014 --> 00:44:04,183
then even this place
is no different from Hell

669
00:44:04,933 --> 00:44:06,101
to him.

670
00:44:07,728 --> 00:44:11,732
We gave him
the most painful punishment possible.

671
00:44:12,691 --> 00:44:14,109
Paternal love.

672
00:44:16,320 --> 00:44:18,864
He never knew that feeling in life,

673
00:44:19,448 --> 00:44:22,618
yet he received it here as punishment.

674
00:44:22,701 --> 00:44:25,829
He'll be thoroughly condemned by you

675
00:44:25,913 --> 00:44:30,417
and feel all your sadness and pain.

676
00:44:34,171 --> 00:44:35,255
I'm sorry.

677
00:44:36,215 --> 00:44:37,299
Forgive me.

678
00:44:38,425 --> 00:44:39,426
Damn it.

679
00:44:41,136 --> 00:44:42,471
You're no father.

680
00:44:43,639 --> 00:44:44,890
How have you been?

681
00:44:45,516 --> 00:44:48,352
"Did he finally return with the money
to take me home?"

682
00:44:49,311 --> 00:44:51,230
"I guess he does care about me after all."

683
00:44:52,147 --> 00:44:53,148
But you know what?

684
00:44:54,233 --> 00:44:55,901
He had actually come by for more money.

685
00:44:56,819 --> 00:45:00,322
He told her he would pay up
since his daughter was in her care.

686
00:45:03,033 --> 00:45:04,118
That's when I knew

687
00:45:05,119 --> 00:45:06,912
I should've never been born.

688
00:45:08,747 --> 00:45:09,748
I shouldn't have.

689
00:45:17,005 --> 00:45:18,924
So why must I

690
00:45:19,716 --> 00:45:20,884
forgive him?

691
00:45:23,011 --> 00:45:24,346
The right to forgive

692
00:45:25,472 --> 00:45:27,141
and the right not to forgive

693
00:45:28,183 --> 00:45:29,935
both belong entirely to you.

694
00:45:31,937 --> 00:45:32,771
However,

695
00:45:33,981 --> 00:45:36,191
regardless of your decision,

696
00:45:36,275 --> 00:45:37,276
your father…

697
00:45:37,776 --> 00:45:39,361
will be reincarnated.

698
00:45:41,321 --> 00:45:42,322
Reincarnated?

699
00:45:43,991 --> 00:45:46,243
You're giving this man another chance?

700
00:45:46,326 --> 00:45:47,578
He doesn't deserve it.

701
00:45:47,661 --> 00:45:50,122
What do you think
is the purpose of reincarnation?

702
00:45:51,206 --> 00:45:54,084
He'll deal with the remaining sins

703
00:45:55,127 --> 00:45:56,378
that even the fires of Hell

704
00:45:56,920 --> 00:45:58,505
couldn't completely burn away.

705
00:45:58,589 --> 00:45:59,590
In other words,

706
00:46:00,340 --> 00:46:01,842
it's about being reborn

707
00:46:02,551 --> 00:46:03,677
to correct and resolve

708
00:46:04,470 --> 00:46:06,972
the mistakes made in the past.

709
00:46:07,764 --> 00:46:10,309
That is the very purpose of reincarnation.

710
00:46:12,686 --> 00:46:14,021
Then what difference

711
00:46:15,022 --> 00:46:18,150
does it make whether I forgive him or not?

712
00:46:18,942 --> 00:46:24,490
You too will carry on living
with all those memories

713
00:46:24,573 --> 00:46:26,325
buried deep in your subconscious.

714
00:46:27,075 --> 00:46:28,869
If you haven't forgiven him,

715
00:46:30,120 --> 00:46:32,956
you'll keep carrying that wounded memory

716
00:46:33,999 --> 00:46:35,751
as you repeat your life.

717
00:46:39,963 --> 00:46:40,964
It's not fair.

718
00:46:41,798 --> 00:46:43,133
I'm sure it's upsetting.

719
00:46:44,426 --> 00:46:47,763
That's why reincarnation must happen.

720
00:46:47,846 --> 00:46:50,140
Because it can't be finished
in just one lifetime.

721
00:46:52,684 --> 00:46:55,354
Are you saying this connection
I desperately want to sever

722
00:46:55,437 --> 00:46:56,939
will continue on?

723
00:46:57,022 --> 00:46:57,940
Yes.

724
00:46:58,982 --> 00:47:00,776
It has continued

725
00:47:00,859 --> 00:47:02,903
and will continue in the future.

726
00:47:04,947 --> 00:47:06,073
For your information,

727
00:47:06,156 --> 00:47:08,909
you and your father…

728
00:47:10,452 --> 00:47:11,537
were husband and wife

729
00:47:12,538 --> 00:47:13,872
in the past.

730
00:47:16,708 --> 00:47:17,834
What did you just say?

731
00:47:18,919 --> 00:47:21,421
It wasn't a very happy ending.

732
00:47:22,422 --> 00:47:25,592
But perhaps you two met again
as parent and child to resolve

733
00:47:26,260 --> 00:47:28,387
the unfinished business
of that connection.

734
00:47:30,222 --> 00:47:33,976
Though that ending
wasn't beautiful either.

735
00:47:35,185 --> 00:47:36,853
If that's my fate,

736
00:47:37,896 --> 00:47:40,023
I'd rather not be reborn at all.

737
00:47:41,275 --> 00:47:44,278
Surely, you don't think
the victim of this fate…

738
00:47:47,030 --> 00:47:48,865
is only you.

739
00:47:50,450 --> 00:47:51,451
Do you?

740
00:47:53,954 --> 00:47:54,955
Who else

741
00:47:55,956 --> 00:47:56,873
is involved?

742
00:49:07,027 --> 00:49:07,944
Young-ae.

743
00:49:10,530 --> 00:49:11,365
That's enough.

744
00:49:12,282 --> 00:49:14,284
Carry the burden of your own sins.

745
00:49:15,243 --> 00:49:16,745
I'll carry mine.

746
00:49:18,705 --> 00:49:20,415
Atone for your sins all your life.

747
00:49:24,753 --> 00:49:26,463
Do you know who's the most pitiful?

748
00:49:29,216 --> 00:49:31,426
We're not worthy
of begging that child for forgiveness.

749
00:49:34,221 --> 00:49:35,055
Does this mean

750
00:49:36,139 --> 00:49:37,391
you've forgiven me?

751
00:49:41,603 --> 00:49:42,771
That's right.

752
00:49:42,854 --> 00:49:45,440
You really have to be
this shameless to be abandoned

753
00:49:46,233 --> 00:49:48,026
by both of your daughters in a row.

754
00:50:04,167 --> 00:50:05,001
You

755
00:50:06,002 --> 00:50:07,170
were my greed.

756
00:50:11,425 --> 00:50:12,467
I was sick and tired

757
00:50:13,510 --> 00:50:15,554
of smiling at men

758
00:50:16,263 --> 00:50:17,681
and selling them drinks.

759
00:50:20,225 --> 00:50:22,352
That's why I coveted someone else's place.

760
00:50:36,199 --> 00:50:38,702
Everyone used to call me
a whore with no roots.

761
00:50:39,745 --> 00:50:42,080
But when I gave birth to you,
their own flesh and blood,

762
00:50:42,164 --> 00:50:43,582
they gave me the guest room.

763
00:50:55,343 --> 00:50:57,929
They might've given me the master room
had you been a son.

764
00:50:58,847 --> 00:50:59,931
But everything was okay.

765
00:51:01,683 --> 00:51:04,936
Except for your constant crying.

766
00:51:11,985 --> 00:51:15,906
I never held you or breastfed you.

767
00:51:16,656 --> 00:51:17,908
That was my greed too.

768
00:51:18,909 --> 00:51:20,827
I was afraid I'd let myself go
while raising you

769
00:51:20,911 --> 00:51:24,623
and would be abandoned by him
because he didn't want me anymore.

770
00:51:25,791 --> 00:51:26,625
Come on.

771
00:51:33,006 --> 00:51:35,592
You were nursed in the arms of a woman

772
00:51:36,760 --> 00:51:38,220
who wasn't even related to you.

773
00:51:38,303 --> 00:51:40,680
But you amazingly grew so much every day

774
00:51:40,764 --> 00:51:43,433
like grass after the rain.

775
00:51:47,229 --> 00:51:48,063
Telegram.

776
00:51:48,855 --> 00:51:50,106
Coming!

777
00:52:14,047 --> 00:52:15,966
I nestled you in my arms,

778
00:52:16,925 --> 00:52:19,511
and I smelled the sweet scent
of persimmon blossoms.

779
00:52:25,600 --> 00:52:26,434
Oh, dear.

780
00:52:31,815 --> 00:52:33,483
For the first time, I felt a desire.

781
00:52:34,776 --> 00:52:37,195
A desire to become a mother.

782
00:52:39,781 --> 00:52:40,824
We'll go now.

783
00:52:40,907 --> 00:52:44,661
-Okay, be careful. You too.
-Okay.

784
00:52:47,038 --> 00:52:48,081
Have a safe trip.

785
00:52:53,044 --> 00:52:55,964
PARIS WESTERN GOODS SHOP

786
00:52:59,259 --> 00:53:00,343
"I'll put these on you

787
00:53:01,177 --> 00:53:02,554
when I go home."

788
00:53:03,471 --> 00:53:07,142
"We'll hold hands and walk
to the edge of the village together."

789
00:53:08,727 --> 00:53:09,728
"When I go home…"

790
00:53:16,610 --> 00:53:19,696
No, my son!

791
00:53:23,241 --> 00:53:27,162
How could you leave me?!

792
00:53:28,079 --> 00:53:29,080
"When I go home…"

793
00:53:32,500 --> 00:53:33,668
"When I go back home…"

794
00:54:21,967 --> 00:54:22,968
My daughter.

795
00:54:24,469 --> 00:54:25,470
Hae-sook.

796
00:54:37,857 --> 00:54:38,858
My sweet girl.

797
00:54:41,152 --> 00:54:44,739
I need to hold you while you sleep too.

798
00:54:56,167 --> 00:54:57,669
That was our connection.

799
00:54:59,587 --> 00:55:00,839
You still

800
00:55:02,007 --> 00:55:03,508
took me in

801
00:55:04,884 --> 00:55:05,969
and fed me.

802
00:55:09,889 --> 00:55:10,974
We can't…

803
00:55:13,226 --> 00:55:14,144
stay like this

804
00:55:15,311 --> 00:55:17,480
forever, can we?

805
00:55:25,530 --> 00:55:26,781
I wish

806
00:55:27,490 --> 00:55:30,076
to sleep beside you like this forever.

807
00:55:31,327 --> 00:55:32,162
Yes.

808
00:55:33,329 --> 00:55:34,581
I'm just being selfish.

809
00:55:36,499 --> 00:55:37,959
Don't forgive me.

810
00:55:39,252 --> 00:55:41,921
Don't you dare forgive your mom.

811
00:56:49,739 --> 00:56:50,824
Are you up?

812
00:56:52,033 --> 00:56:53,201
Oh, this?

813
00:56:53,284 --> 00:56:54,786
You and I are going out today.

814
00:56:55,829 --> 00:56:58,456
I packed some gimbap, your favorite.
Sounds good, right?

815
00:57:00,083 --> 00:57:00,917
Yes.

816
00:57:08,800 --> 00:57:10,510
It feels surreal.

817
00:57:11,177 --> 00:57:15,223
I can't even tell if I'm alive or dead.

818
00:57:17,433 --> 00:57:21,312
I wish I had thought of coming
to nice places with you earlier.

819
00:57:21,396 --> 00:57:23,982
We should've done this sooner.

820
00:57:25,775 --> 00:57:28,361
I'm just glad we're here now.

821
00:57:29,737 --> 00:57:34,784
I always felt sorry
that I made you do harsh things only.

822
00:57:35,869 --> 00:57:37,120
Don't be like that.

823
00:57:37,203 --> 00:57:38,621
I did it because I wanted to.

824
00:57:40,331 --> 00:57:42,459
I liked being with you.

825
00:57:46,588 --> 00:57:48,173
I was never comfortable

826
00:57:48,256 --> 00:57:52,218
with physical contact
with anyone but my husband.

827
00:57:53,678 --> 00:57:56,848
But strangely, with you,
I didn't mind it right from the start.

828
00:57:57,849 --> 00:57:59,726
I don't know if you remember.

829
00:58:00,518 --> 00:58:02,395
But you snuggled up
right next to me at night

830
00:58:02,479 --> 00:58:04,314
from the very day I brought you home.

831
00:58:05,565 --> 00:58:06,733
Did I?

832
00:58:07,358 --> 00:58:10,195
I was startled when you reached out
your hand while I was sleeping.

833
00:58:11,821 --> 00:58:16,743
But what surprised me more was
how rough your small hands were.

834
00:58:18,453 --> 00:58:21,831
They were so chapped and rougher
than a construction worker's hands.

835
00:58:22,749 --> 00:58:25,502
But despite being young,
you were still loyal.

836
00:58:26,211 --> 00:58:27,378
-Loyal?
-Yes.

837
00:58:28,004 --> 00:58:31,174
You knew where your father was.

838
00:58:32,467 --> 00:58:33,676
But you played dumb

839
00:58:33,760 --> 00:58:37,597
and refused to tell me where he was
since he was still your father.

840
00:58:40,517 --> 00:58:41,351
You're wrong.

841
00:58:42,185 --> 00:58:43,019
It was the opposite.

842
00:58:45,230 --> 00:58:48,024
I was afraid that you might find him

843
00:58:49,692 --> 00:58:51,027
and tell him to take me back.

844
00:58:53,363 --> 00:58:56,115
It wasn't that I was scared
of going back to that house.

845
00:58:57,116 --> 00:58:59,994
I just didn't want
to be separated from you.

846
00:59:01,955 --> 00:59:04,499
But I didn't even treat you that well.

847
00:59:06,334 --> 00:59:07,168
You're wrong.

848
00:59:08,419 --> 00:59:11,589
You took in a complete stranger.

849
00:59:13,091 --> 00:59:14,050
You raised me

850
00:59:15,843 --> 00:59:18,763
and treated me
as if I was your own daughter.

851
00:59:22,433 --> 00:59:24,352
So of course you treated me well.

852
00:59:25,812 --> 00:59:26,980
If anything, it's me.

853
00:59:29,274 --> 00:59:30,858
I have sinned so much.

854
00:59:31,943 --> 00:59:34,070
There's nothing I ever did for you.

855
00:59:35,530 --> 00:59:38,575
Nothing… I couldn't do anything for you.

856
00:59:40,827 --> 00:59:41,995
Don't be silly.

857
00:59:44,247 --> 00:59:46,833
You must try to live happily from now on.

858
00:59:48,251 --> 00:59:51,421
Find someone
who's absolutely head over heels for you.

859
00:59:51,504 --> 00:59:54,716
You should fight and make up.

860
00:59:55,300 --> 00:59:58,469
Have kids
and have your heart broken at times.

861
00:59:59,596 --> 01:00:03,391
Live your life naturally
like flowing water.

862
01:00:09,230 --> 01:00:10,857
Go back down

863
01:00:11,983 --> 01:00:13,151
and live that kind of life.

864
01:00:14,944 --> 01:00:16,195
Later,

865
01:00:17,280 --> 01:00:22,201
when you've lived so long that
you're tired of waking up every morning…

866
01:00:23,411 --> 01:00:24,454
Then,

867
01:00:25,163 --> 01:00:27,081
let's meet again. Promise.

868
01:00:35,173 --> 01:00:36,007
And

869
01:00:37,008 --> 01:00:38,301
next time,

870
01:00:39,052 --> 01:00:42,055
shower me with your love, Mom.

871
01:01:00,406 --> 01:01:01,240
Mom…

872
01:01:02,950 --> 01:01:08,081
Mom…

873
01:01:22,345 --> 01:01:26,432
LEE HAE-SOOK'S LIST

874
01:01:50,081 --> 01:01:50,915
Ms. Lee?

875
01:01:53,835 --> 01:01:56,295
Ms. Lee, are you awake?

876
01:02:01,843 --> 01:02:04,554
You've been unconscious for three months.

877
01:02:25,700 --> 01:02:27,201
Did I do well?

878
01:02:29,036 --> 01:02:31,539
You couldn't have done better.

879
01:02:33,416 --> 01:02:35,835
Did you come because you were worried?

880
01:02:40,840 --> 01:02:43,426
Are you saying Young-ae is my birth mother

881
01:02:44,010 --> 01:02:48,139
and her father who abandoned her
is my birth father?

882
01:02:49,599 --> 01:02:51,058
This is just ridiculous.

883
01:02:51,642 --> 01:02:53,019
Do you expect me to believe that?

884
01:02:54,353 --> 01:02:57,231
Do you have
some kind of grudge against me?

885
01:02:58,149 --> 01:02:59,984
It was like this
with my mother-in-law too.

886
01:03:00,568 --> 01:03:02,236
If what you're saying is true,

887
01:03:02,987 --> 01:03:06,115
who can I possibly blame
even if I suffer unfair treatment?

888
01:03:07,408 --> 01:03:12,538
Because you're saying that person
will always be connected to me somehow.

889
01:03:13,623 --> 01:03:15,708
Yes, that's correct.

890
01:03:16,459 --> 01:03:19,462
Whether you're seeking the reason
for present happiness

891
01:03:20,129 --> 01:03:21,464
or past misfortune,

892
01:03:22,089 --> 01:03:26,010
the law of fate can provide the answer.

893
01:03:27,804 --> 01:03:29,472
Do you feel like it's unfair?

894
01:03:29,555 --> 01:03:31,307
Yes, I do.

895
01:03:32,517 --> 01:03:35,353
Your birth mother basically abandoned you,

896
01:03:35,436 --> 01:03:37,271
and you ended up taking care of her.

897
01:03:37,939 --> 01:03:40,399
-That's what you feel is unfair, isn't it?
-Of course.

898
01:03:41,192 --> 01:03:43,528
I wouldn't have taken her in
if I knew that.

899
01:03:44,862 --> 01:03:45,988
So tell me.

900
01:03:46,072 --> 01:03:49,575
How was the time
you spent with Young-ae in ignorance?

901
01:03:50,159 --> 01:03:51,244
Were you miserable?

902
01:03:52,161 --> 01:03:53,412
Was it only full of pain?

903
01:03:58,251 --> 01:04:01,295
I thought about what you said.

904
01:04:01,963 --> 01:04:05,424
I realized that
I actually received more than I gave.

905
01:04:08,094 --> 01:04:09,846
She was my friend on ordinary days.

906
01:04:09,929 --> 01:04:11,430
Do you have a death wish?

907
01:04:11,514 --> 01:04:14,350
She was like an older sister
when a fight broke out.

908
01:04:16,769 --> 01:04:18,271
And when I was sick,

909
01:04:18,855 --> 01:04:20,273
she was like a mom.

910
01:04:24,694 --> 01:04:29,240
I started thinking,
"I think I can understand."

911
01:04:30,950 --> 01:04:34,787
It's normal for a child
to expect things from their parents.

912
01:04:36,205 --> 01:04:39,834
After all, they're older
and gave birth to us.

913
01:04:41,919 --> 01:04:43,838
But when I think about it,

914
01:04:44,547 --> 01:04:47,341
that life was a first for her too.

915
01:04:48,843 --> 01:04:52,555
It was her first time being a mom.

916
01:04:53,681 --> 01:04:55,349
So she must've been inexperienced

917
01:04:55,933 --> 01:04:57,685
and afraid.

918
01:05:01,939 --> 01:05:03,107
I prayed…

919
01:05:05,610 --> 01:05:08,821
that I could bless my mother
and feel no resentment.

920
01:05:10,323 --> 01:05:12,241
That I could even be grateful.

921
01:05:15,369 --> 01:05:17,914
I know Young-ae will be happy.

922
01:05:20,458 --> 01:05:23,669
"Whatever you ask for in prayer,

923
01:05:24,503 --> 01:05:26,839
believe that you have received it."

924
01:05:29,884 --> 01:05:34,555
I felt in my heart
that Young-ae was living happily.

925
01:05:36,015 --> 01:05:38,517
I rejoiced as if it had already happened.

926
01:05:39,101 --> 01:05:41,312
And I gave thanks.

927
01:05:43,648 --> 01:05:44,649
I pray.

928
01:05:51,822 --> 01:05:53,282
Mom.

929
01:05:53,366 --> 01:05:57,119
That at the end of suffering lies
enlightenment that's equal to its weight.

930
01:06:02,500 --> 01:06:04,251
For the preciousness
of the smallest things.

931
01:06:04,335 --> 01:06:06,504
-Ring, ring, coming through
-Ring, ring, coming through

932
01:06:12,218 --> 01:06:15,262
That what I earnestly desired
has already been possessed.

933
01:06:47,753 --> 01:06:48,587
And…

934
01:06:50,715 --> 01:06:52,633
I thank you that my prayers

935
01:06:54,260 --> 01:06:55,344
have already been answered.

936
01:07:15,156 --> 01:07:15,990
Mom.

937
01:07:25,541 --> 01:07:26,625
Eun-ho…

938
01:07:26,709 --> 01:07:29,295
My baby, Eun-ho…

939
01:07:55,946 --> 01:07:59,033
HEAVENLY EVER AFTER

940
01:07:59,116 --> 01:08:01,827
Honey, I've found something
I really want to do.

941
01:08:01,911 --> 01:08:03,287
It's that Heaven's Lottery thing.

942
01:08:04,330 --> 01:08:08,459
Where might the key
to unlocking my heart be hidden?

943
01:08:09,376 --> 01:08:10,252
Maybe this way?

944
01:08:10,336 --> 01:08:12,296
I don't know who I am.

945
01:08:12,379 --> 01:08:14,924
But you do, don't you?

946
01:08:15,007 --> 01:08:16,592
Who you are isn't important.

947
01:08:17,176 --> 01:08:18,928
So don't bother Hae-sook
with this nonsense.

948
01:08:20,096 --> 01:08:23,849
It's a key. You are truly incredible!

949
01:08:23,933 --> 01:08:25,434
That child, Eun-ho…

950
01:08:25,518 --> 01:08:27,394
-I think…
-Mom!

951
01:08:27,478 --> 01:08:28,854
…he was my son…

952
01:08:30,064 --> 01:08:31,232
What do you mean?

953
01:08:31,315 --> 01:08:32,233
Is your memory back?

954
01:08:34,110 --> 01:08:35,027
Open the door!

955
01:08:35,111 --> 01:08:37,571
Eun-ho. Why my son?

956
